article.headline: UC Irvine 70, Sam Houston State 62 (OT)
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Chuma Awaji had 15 points and 14 rebounds and Darren Fells had 14 points as UC Irvine beat Sam Houston State 70-62 in overtime Saturday night. Nic Campbell added 10 points for UC Irvine (4-6), which had lost four of five coming into the game. Tied at 56 at the end of regulation, the Anteaters outscored the Bearkats 14-6 in the extra period. Jejuan Plair led Sam Houston State (6-4) with 16 points, and Jeremy Thomas had 10. The Bearkats play No. 1 UCLA on Tuesday.
